HEADWORD: Delitescency
<hw>Del`i*tes"cen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Concealment;
seclusion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mental organization of the novelist must be characterized, to
speak craniologically, by an extraordinary development of the passion
for <qex>delitescency</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Delitescent</ent>⟦br⟧
